cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with improving search engine results by detecting and adapting to shifts in intent of search queries. This falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as well as Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) since the paper discusses using classifiers to understand the intent of queries. The use of bandit algorithms to optimize search results falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the impact of news events and pop culture on search queries, which could fall under the category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as well.
